What Surprised Me Most:

-Scale of Crime: Phishing remains the #1 cyber threat globally, with nearly 300,000 complaints in the FBI’s 2023 report.
Psychological Warfare: Attackers don't just "hack" computers; they hack humans using fear and urgency (e.g., "Account Suspended").
Sophistication: Scams now use "pixel-perfect" clones of official banking and university portals that are nearly impossible to distinguish from the real thing.
-The "Golden Hour": The critical importance of reporting UPI fraud within 2 hours to the 1930 helpline to freeze stolen funds.

Personal Habit Change:

-Ending Password Reuse: I will stop using the same password for my college portal and personal accounts to prevent a "domino effect" breach.
-Using a Password Manager: I will switch to a dedicated manager to generate and store unique, complex credentials for every site.
-Activating 2FA: I am enabling Two-Factor Authentication on all sensitive accounts, moving from SMS codes to more secure Authenticator apps.
